00300                 B3_FORCE_INLINE void reserve(int _Count)
00301                 {       // determine new minimum length of allocated storage
00302                         if (capacity() < _Count)
00303                         {       // not enough room, reallocate
00304                                 T*      s = (T*)allocate(_Count);
00305                                 b3Assert(s);
00306                                 if (s==0)
00307                                 {
00308                                         b3Error("b3AlignedObjectArray reserve out-of-memory\n");
00309                                         _Count=0;
00310                                         m_size=0;
00311                                 }
00312                                 copy(0, size(), s);
00313 
00314                                 destroy(0,size());
00315 
00316                                 deallocate();
00317                                 
00318                                 //PCK: added this line
00319                                 m_ownsMemory = true;
00320 
00321                                 m_data = s;
00322                                 
00323                                 m_capacity = _Count;
00324 
00325                         }
00326                 }

00340                 template <typename L>
00341                 void quickSortInternal(const L& CompareFunc,int lo, int hi)
00342                 {
00343                 //  lo is the lower index, hi is the upper index
00344                 //  of the region of array a that is to be sorted
00345                         int i=lo, j=hi;
00346                         T x=m_data[(lo+hi)/2];
00347 
00348                         //  partition
00349                         do
00350                         {    
00351                                 while (CompareFunc(m_data[i],x)) 
00352                                         i++; 
00353                                 while (CompareFunc(x,m_data[j])) 
00354                                         j--;
00355                                 if (i<=j)
00356                                 {
00357                                         swap(i,j);
00358                                         i++; j--;
00359                                 }
00360                         } while (i<=j);
00361 
00362                         //  recursion
00363                         if (lo<j) 
00364                                 quickSortInternal( CompareFunc, lo, j);
00365                         if (i<hi) 
00366                                 quickSortInternal( CompareFunc, i, hi);
00367                 }

00382                 template <typename L>
00383                 void downHeap(T *pArr, int k, int n, const L& CompareFunc)
00384                 {
00385                         /*  PRE: a[k+1..N] is a heap */
00386                         /* POST:  a[k..N]  is a heap */
00387                         
00388                         T temp = pArr[k - 1];
00389                         /* k has child(s) */
00390                         while (k <= n/2) 
00391                         {
00392                                 int child = 2*k;
00393                                 
00394                                 if ((child < n) && CompareFunc(pArr[child - 1] , pArr[child]))
00395                                 {
00396                                         child++;
00397                                 }
00398                                 /* pick larger child */
00399                                 if (CompareFunc(temp , pArr[child - 1]))
00400                                 {
00401                                         /* move child up */
00402                                         pArr[k - 1] = pArr[child - 1];
00403                                         k = child;
00404                                 }
00405                                 else
00406                                 {
00407                                         break;
00408                                 }
00409                         }
00410                         pArr[k - 1] = temp;
00411                 } /*downHeap*/

00413                 void    swap(int index0,int index1)
00414                 {
00415 #ifdef B3_USE_MEMCPY
00416                         char    temp[sizeof(T)];
00417                         memcpy(temp,&m_data[index0],sizeof(T));
00418                         memcpy(&m_data[index0],&m_data[index1],sizeof(T));
00419                         memcpy(&m_data[index1],temp,sizeof(T));
00420 #else
00421                         T temp = m_data[index0];
00422                         m_data[index0] = m_data[index1];
00423                         m_data[index1] = temp;
00424 #endif //B3_USE_PLACEMENT_NEW
00425 
00426                 }

00428         template <typename L>
00429         void heapSort(const L& CompareFunc)
00430         {
00431                 /* sort a[0..N-1],  N.B. 0 to N-1 */
00432                 int k;
00433                 int n = m_size;
00434                 for (k = n/2; k > 0; k--) 
00435                 {
00436                         downHeap(m_data, k, n, CompareFunc);
00437                 }
00438 
00439                 /* a[1..N] is now a heap */
00440                 while ( n>=1 ) 
00441                 {
00442                         swap(0,n-1); /* largest of a[0..n-1] */
00443 
00444 
00445                         n = n - 1;
00446                         /* restore a[1..i-1] heap */
00447                         downHeap(m_data, 1, n, CompareFunc);
00448                 } 
00449         }

00452         int     findBinarySearch(const T& key) const
00453         {
00454                 int first = 0;
00455                 int last = size()-1;
00456 
00457                 //assume sorted array
00458                 while (first <= last) {
00459                         int mid = (first + last) / 2;  // compute mid point.
00460                         if (key > m_data[mid]) 
00461                                 first = mid + 1;  // repeat search in top half.
00462                         else if (key < m_data[mid]) 
00463                                 last = mid - 1; // repeat search in bottom half.
00464                         else
00465                                 return mid;     // found it. return position /////
00466                 }
00467                 return size();    // failed to find key
00468         }
